Aramco Issues $7 Billion of Contracts for Wasit, Riyadh Reports

-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 
2011-04-09T15:01:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-09/aramco-issues-7-billion-of-contracts-for-wasit-riyadh-reports.html
Saudi Aramco has spent around 26.3
billion Saudi riyals ($7 billion) on contracts to develop the
Wasit offshore natural-gas field, al-Riyadh  said , citing Khalid
Halwani, a consultant at a sub-contracting company involved with
the project.  Italy’s  Saipem SpA (SPM)  got the main contract for drilling,
extracting and recovering gas from the field, valued at 17.2
billion riyals, Halwani told the newspaper.  Korean SK Engineering & Construction Co. received a
contract worth 7.1 billion riyals to build facilities for the
Wasit natural-gas plant, while the rest of the main contracts
went to  Korea ’s Samsung Engineering Co., according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar at 
